caption: I may be a ramen convert. Nothing fancy, but delicious...and I've had ramen in Japan!
Tonkotsu Ramen + Ajitama Egg + (love that garlic) Garlic Gyoza
Amazing ramen! They have gluten free and vegetarian options, both delicious. Our new go to spot for ramen!!
I’m Japanese so when it comes to ramen I’m pretty picky.. but hey Their ramen is incredibly delicious!! I felt like I was in Japan. Definitely come back again! Try Gyoza too!
I love the Ramen! Its the best I've ever had.
Little pricey but the ramen is so rich and flavorful. There are vegetarian options for the broths.
Super good TanTanMen, as good as I've had in America. All of the ramen is authentic and the owner is Japanese.
Great food and service.
Yum
Great räumen and great service

Very tasteful restaurant and very fast.  I didn't receive any special service and they demanded a tip for service. This sucks being that I'm already spending over $20 for a bowl of ramen. You try to support local business and it's never enough. So make sure you have cash to tip.
Solid ramen. I wouldn't say it's my favorite, but if someone else did, I wouldn't bat an eye.
Really great food! I highly recommend the quesadillas!!!!
Pretty good ramen place. Usually our go-to spot.  I recommend this location if you enjoy ramen.  Parking: On Young St behind the building, there’s a large parking lot, usually free of charge.
I liked it but my girl got sick from the egg. The boied eggs are runny in the middle. I'm sure that's culturally correct but weird to us tourists

Just missing that taste of authenticity. Tastes like store bought noodles, store bought katsu sauce. Huge let down. They need to be more creative with their pork cutlet burger. Its a 15 dollar slider with store bought tonkatsu sauce. This is a mediocre Ramen spot.
Nice taste and great service.  Portions could be slightly larger, especially for the potato salad.  Would definitely recommend, especially their specials if you can get them before they sell out

(Translated by Google) Right next to the Honolulu Museum of Art. The shop was very kind and I was able to eat comfortably. This time I had dandan noodles, tomato ramen, and dumplings, all of which were delicious. Especially tomato ramen had less tonkotsu and the soup was delicious and I liked it. The skin of the dumplings is crispy, and the inside is filled with bean paste. There are seats inside and outside the shop.  (Original) ホノルル美術館のすぐそば。お店の方がとても親切で気持ちよくお食事できました。 今回は坦々麺、トマトラーメン、餃子をいただきましたがどれも美味しかったです。特にトマトラーメンはとんこつ感が少なくスープが美味しくて自分の好みでした。餃子も皮はパリパリ、中は餡が詰まってます。 お店の中と外に席があり。
username: かわいいヒナキンちゃん

caption: (Translated by Google) delicious! I've been eating various ramen in Hawaii and it's pretty good. The inside of the store is clean and the clerk is kind. It is energetic because it is popular even in severe situations due to the corona storm. I ate dandan noodles and tomato ramen. I would like to come again ^ _ ^  (Original) 美味しい！ハワイでいろいろラーメンを食べ歩いてるが、かなり良いです。 店内もキレイで店員も優しいです。 コロナ禍で厳しい状況でも人気があるので元気があります。 坦々麺とトマトラーメンを食べました。 また来たいと思います^_^

Miso ramen very tasty. Noodles were firm and not too chewy. Pork and bamboo shoots goes well with the miso dashi. Garlic gyoza along with shoyu vinegar sauce was very good. A/C was very cold and stool seats had no back support. Service was quick and friendly.
Decent place to visit and have fun with friends and family in a free time or on a weekends. Services are at reasonable cost with best offers on dishes.

(Translated by Google) I heard the reputation and went. Tandan noodles and soup had a very rich body and were delicious. Sesame sweetness can be mixed with spicy soup. Lots of vegetables. However, it was black tonkotsu that tasted better than this Tandan noodles. The char siu is tasteful and tastes good oil. Garlic is effective and delicious. If you ask for only one item next time, I think you will order black tonkotsu. The interior is very stylish with jazz playing. There are indoor and outdoor seats. It was good that customer service was also exciting. The parking lot enters from Young Street side.  (Original) 評判を聞きつけて行ってきました。 担々麺、スープはなかなか深みのあるコクがあって美味しかったです。ごまの甘みがピリ辛のスープと混ぜ合わされて良いです。野菜もたくさん。 しかし、この坦々麺よりもおいしかったのは黒とんこつ。チャーシューは味が染みていて程良い油分が美味。ガーリックが効いていておいしい。次回一品だけ頼むとすれば黒とんこつをオーダーすると思います。 店内はジャズが流れていたりして、なかなかおしゃれな雰囲気。室内席と室外席があります。 接客もハキハキしていて良かったです。 駐車場はYoung Street側から入ります。
Awesome food, Awesome service. Will definitely be back
I love their Ramen! So flavorful and filling! Friendly service every time. I’m going to keep coming back for more!
By far the best ramen in Hawaii for a decent price. BONUS: They have two Vegetarian Options that are delicious. their homemade chips are perfectly thin and crunchy all the time.
Good rich broth. Could've gone hotter but that's up to you.

love this neighborhood ramen spot! great customer service, friendly staff, & unique menu selection. also good for takeout.  my favorites: cold tan tan noodles karaage chicken gyoza homemade potato chips!  pro tip: this is a popular preshow dinner spot whenever there are events at the Blaisdell. be sure to go early to grab a table if that's your plan.
Friendly staff and if dining it, you feel safe with the partitions between the tables. The food is Soooo GOOD!!!
Fom a 1-10 it was a 20. Love Junpuu

I'd been excited to eat their Ramen and they didn't betray at all. The soup is good, noodles are good too. I like more skinny noodles and their soup is lil bit too salty personally. My husband and I got one bowl of Garlic Tonkotsu and extra full noodles $3, and they gave us extra small bowl to share it. That's worth it and you can save money. We also ate spicy cheese gyoza and there was a lot of cheese on it, so delicious. I'd like to try Tantan next time.
Fast service
Very delicious ramen! I'll eat this again next week again!
Great. Don't underestimate the spice levels though. Haha
Good prices on meals and nice noodles.

This is MY FAVORITE RAMEN ON OAHU! I get level 6 out of 10, i like the kick but can still eat it and enjoy it. Lol. I like the tantan min, sesame flavor. I get the special with is extra Char Sui and a soft boiled egg plus i add more bamboo shoots. I always get the full Char Sui quesadilla so i can take half home for a snack. The gyoza is bomb, i get the garlic which is COVERED in garlic chips!

This is probably my favorite place to get ramen in Honolulu. But I've noticed the service starting to slip. Everyone use to be so nice and welcoming. Now I've noticed that they're mocking and kind of rude. In the last 3 times I've been there, I've ordered an Ajitama egg on the side and when I got my ramen, I noticed it wasnt there but I was charged for it. I'm really sad about the progression that they seems to be going in.
Great food all the time
(Translated by Google) Slurpnom  (Original) Slurpnom

Junpuu our go to place for Japanese Ramen. A hole in the wall type of joint that brings out some of the best ramen my wife and I can enjoy on Oahu. Staff is really friendly. Tan tan is probably the best here but all flavors are still tasty. We definitely recommend to anyone seeking some awesome ramen. Even though I give it a 5 star I still would recommend Junpuu upgrading their charsui. Other than that it’s a five in our eyes.

The chicken karaage was great.  Thoroughly disappointed with our garlic miso ramen and spicy miso ramen.  The noodles were the biggest disappointment.  Weren't expecting saimin type of noodles. Checked this off of my places to try list.
Love their tonkatsu ramen!
The ramen is good, and the appetizers are an interesting idea, but neither is outstanding.
I love strong and oily ramen broth. Junpuu got it.

I prefer the vegetarian tartan ramen but they do not put as many different vegetables in it like they used to. Also it looks like less actual soup is in the bowl but that may not be a fact. They do not have an option for a small bowl of just broth for less than 5 bucks. Gyoza nice, chicken karagi also. No good dipping sauce for either. They have a house dessert that is fantastic. Creamy tofu almond flavor like a pudding

One of the best ramens in downtown. The vegetarian ramen is delicious and you can barely tell that it’s vegetarian because there is so much umami. The takoyaki are okay but nothing on par like what you get in Osaka.

For Vegetarians, Must try their vegetarian ramen options, especially Vegetarian Tantan Men. You can also ask for spice level. I recommend level 6.  Amazing place! The location is also nice. Also, try their dessert, comes with a surprising taste!
Overrated garlic tonkotsu ramen was very salty!  Service is bad, we were not greeted upon entering. Food is over priced! Don't go here!!! Gyoza pork meat was still pink not cooked well.
I enjoy their ramen offers but this time  tried something different.  Had the char sui quesadilla  and gyoza.   Yummy!
Vegan options are good. Interesting flavors!
My guy feeling is that the new kitchen guy is still a bit rough...

Good location next to Thomas Square city park with streetcurb parking.  Clean tiny cafe with both inside and outside dining tables.  Courteous, good service.  Ramen soup is too salty and fatty for our palates.
Really enjoy Junpuu! The specialty ramen are very tasty! Would go back again to try more of the menu!

Junpuu has a delicious Vegetarian Tan Tan, which is actually vegan! I love the unique toppings they have (spinach, kabocha pumpkin, red bell pepper, bamboo shoots, green beans, zucchini, and eggplant). The staff is very kind and helpful.  Also a huge plus that the building has parking in the back.  I've never had to drive around looking for parking when coming here!
I got a level 10. Felt the heat, but the broth was too good to be overwhelmed. 🔥
Good service and one of the best ramen stops on the island and it's a hole I'm the wall kinda a feel love it
Great flavor. Nice Staff.

Junpuu is a great place to enjoy a very tasty bowl of Ramen with very good service! The portion size is just enough to make you full and wishing there was more!  I had a bowl of their brown sugar pudding that was so amazing and the perfect finish after a bowl of Ramen.  I will definitely be back again and again!!
Hands down one of the freshest and most interesting Ramen spots on Oahu! Even the vegetarian Ramen broth has some serious depth!
The food was awesome! We ordered the quesadilla, the pork burger and the shoyu ramen and everything was delicious. Service was very efficient and friendly. Just beware there is only 1 bathroom.
Great service ,clean and Excellent food
Very friendly staff and the food was delicious 👍
Excellent
Food was hot and delicious.
Better than Agu, not as good as Hokkaido
Delish! Order the takoyaki.
Amazing ramen.  Be aware, it is BYOB.  There is a Long's Drugs right next door.
Nice place to grab food if you need to visit straub. Actually, the food is good enough to go just for a meal.
Delicious OxTail is my absolute favorite. Super Flavorful and OMG tender ...

Fantastic experience at Junpuu! I safely ate here as a celiac with no issues. The employee who served us (I wish I had gotten her name!) was very helpful and knowledgeable when it came to my allergy issues and assisted me in ordering some super yummy ramen with rice noodles! My kids were also happy with their meals, as was my husband. We currently live in Japan and will be in Hawaii for a couple of weeks. It was nice finding somewhere to extend a friendly “Kon'nichiwa” and “Arigatōgozaimashita” to some awesome Japanese folks. Thanks for a great dinner!
Tonkotsu Garlic Ramen!!!!   So good.  Very friendly staff and a clean environment
First time guests, will come again. Miso Ramen is killer. Fast service and accommodating.  Good job
Ramen is great! Just wish the place was bigger.
Excellent,  friendly service and food was  'ono!

I really liked this place. I was hoping to love it but the ramen broth was not quite my style. They had an interesting take on gyoza with the cheesy spicy gyoza and it was really good. My son loved the chicken karage. Service was excellent as well. I'm sure we'll be back again!
Great food, really friendly and helpful service.

My husband and I are on this ramen journey. And my husband loved black garlic ramen. This restaurant had a good amount of choices. We both chose the garlic tonkatsu ramen. I’m not a fan of bamboo shots but it gives it a different depth of flavor so it was good. The tonkatsu was good too. We’re definitely going back because I want to try the spicy ramen next or the garlic miso ramen.
EVERYONE LOVES RAMEN!!!

Talk about fresh noodles and fresh potstickers. It's a small place but their ramen is full of flavor. I got the Spicy Tokyo Tonkotsu Ramen and the gyoza. I usually do not drink the soup but they have it down perfectly here. The soup had the perfect amount of spice accompanying a classic Tonkotsu. If there is a long line... Be patient and you will bless your tastebuds with a heavenly experience.
1st time at this eatery; Onolicious!!

The employees were super friendly and fun to chat with. They gave good recommendations and there was a good variety on the menu for you to choose from. The garlic Parmesan Ramen was definitely pretty solid. The spicy Ramen with peanuts was OK it wasn’t the best. I’d come back and eat around here again though! Nice view of the park sitting outside.
Great service, amazing food!

This is the first time I've tried this place. The restaurant was clean, hip, and the staff was very friendly. I ordered the garlic miso ramen, and it was quite good. The noodles were not soggy. I really liked the texture. It came with 2 pieces of Cha siu. I think they were ok. They had a good proportion of fat and meat, but it was a bit tough. The soup was good. I liked how they added sesame, onions and bamboo shoots. But honestly, I couldn't taste the garlic flavor too much. The one great surprise was the chicken karaage. The chickens were fleshly fried, and the meat was still very juicy. It also came with Himalayan salt. This dish worked really well. I highly recommend it. In general I enjoyed the experience here, and would definitely come back again.
My favorite is the Tan tan and garlic gyoza
Great noodles at this shop!
Great ramen!!!
This place rocks! Great service and killer food!
So yum. The only ramen spot I know that puts finely sliced red onion on ramen... please never stop!
Best ramen in town.  Great gluten free options

This place was awesome! I got the spicy tonkatsu ramen and my girlfriend got the curry and both were delicious. I also ordered a soda and they gave me a large one in a to go cup when I left! Great customer service and very reasonably priced.

While visiting Honolulu, my husband and I were craving some yummy ramen. After a little searching, we converged Junpuu, primarily because of the vegetarian ramen options available for myself. The ramen we had was delicious and the service was awesome! I had the spicy vegetarian tantan ramen, while my husband had the spicy tonkotsu. As someone who loves spicy and normally finds the spiciest level to not be enough, these guys take their spice seriously!!! I got a 7 for mine and was challenged. It was so worth it though. Will definitely return on our next trip to Honolulu!

(Translated by Google) This place is straight fire! Fuego! The flavor is spot on, the broth can be made spicy, and the staff is the best.The fire here is real, though.I get a 5 and it's plenty spicy.You can get a 10 You can get up to a 100 spicy for a small price. Seriously though, if you can go higher than 10 maybe you should see a doctor. But delicious! Really delicious! Although the hotness can be five times higher. I don't wait!  (Original) This place is straight fire! Fuego! The flavor is spot on, the broth can be made spicy, and the staff is the best. The fire here is real, though. I get a 5 and it’s plenty spicy. You can get a 10 spicy included in the spice. You can get up to a 100 spicy for a small price. Seriously though, if you can go higher than 10 maybe you should see a doctor. ラメンはメッチャ辛い！でも、美味い！本当に美味しい！辛さは五倍できるけど。待ったないよ！
Great food good service

It is quite crowded during lunch. People really like it especially workers. Personally, I did not really enjoy the style of noodles, but others may disagree. I did like how you can adjust the level of spiciness to your liking. I got the 10 level spicy which was definitely a challenge. All in all, the soup was great, the toppings were great, the people were great, I just didnt personally enjoy the noodles.
Best ramen on Oahu hands down
Great food, friendly staff
Great spicy ramen and garlic flaked gyoza. Very reasonable prices and excellent service.  Have been here several times and always leave very satisfied.

Good service but the ramen was nothing to write home about: very oily (we’ve tried 3 different soup bases), hardly any toppings (you need to order ala carte for normally included egg and other things) and the noodle portion was very small. We’ve also ordered the char siu quesadilla and it was very oily and very disappointing taste and rather expensive for a small appetizer as well.  Service was good but our family would give this place a D-: over-priced, over-rated and yes, over-loaded with MSG. I would go to Shirokiya Food Court for better ramens.
Top of their game. They bring ramen to a whole new level. A must visit for tourists and local's alike.
First time.. my new favorite ramen shop!! Service is great and quik

Excellent Ramen, good taste and a decent portion size. Good to know, the extra spicy option really does mean extra spicy, be warned. Also  they have vegetarian options which is not a guarantee at ramen places.

The takoyaki was very creamy, super good. I had tan tan ramen at 30x hot. It was perfectly spicy! About like a fresh habenero. They go up to 100x hot.  I might try that someday. The garlic gyoza was superb as well. Definitely going back soon.
place I go for my ramen cravings
very good

Spice level goes up to 100, but I can barely enjoy a 10. This is coming from a guy that complains when the highest spice level from a place is not very hot at all. I would stick with a 5 to 7 range. Great food, portion sizes are nice and big compared to some ramen places nearby. Would highly recommend.
Just might be a New Favorite Ramen spot of mines🤩
One of the best Ajii Tamago.  Many of the food while strange is some of best.
Ramen is really good
One of the best ramen spots on island, to me best spicy tonkotsu , especially that you make as spicy as you want.
Nice atmosphere. Workers turned music down for my sleeping baby

I like their garlic tonkotsu ramen. I'm a big eater so I usually get the extra noodles. the flavor is good and so are the noodles. the price is i in line with the rest of the good ramen shops. the parking is right in front or in back if you can't find metered stalls. if you have an electric car the meters are free. if you go in the late after noon you may want to sit inside since the sunset can get intense. they have tables outside which is pretty nice since it overlooks Thomas Square Park. it's a very chill place. it's good to eat outside before or after the late afternoon. they have gyōza and other appetizers too so it's not just ramen. I like this place and will be going back. they take cash or credit cards. if you sign in on their online computer with your phone number you get free food offers to entice you back.
Very tasty dishes. Gotta try it
Literally the best ramen in my life. There pretty much weekly. It's a problem.

(Translated by Google) One of the few ramen shops in Oahu.  The service is very good and the atmosphere is bright and pleasant.  The chorschuke sadira was very delicious! This combination is good! Cheese dumplings are just relieved with the cheese hanging on the top.  Pork bone noodles are made overseas. A very refreshing soup without any pig's strength. Speaking of tasteless, it is not tasteful, but this is this.  JUNPUU SUPREME homage logo is also nice.  (Original) オアフ島にある数少ないラーメン屋。  サービスはとてもいいし、雰囲気も明るくて気持ちがいい。  チャーシューケサディラがとても美味しかった！この組み合わせはいける！チーズ餃子は上にチーズがドバァとかかっているだけであんまし。  豚骨らーめんは海外ウケする作り。豚のしつこさが全然なく、極めてスッキリしているスープ。味気ないといえば味気ないけど、これはこれ。  JUNPUUのSUPREMEオマージュロゴも素敵。
Delicious spicy tan tan! You can get your ramen up to 100x spicy with the signing of a waiver. Careful. My favorite place to get spicy tantan.

Had the Garlic Miso Ramen...good portion and the flavor was great. Very home style of preparation and decor. Chose hot tea to go with my ramen and they brought a selection of various tea bags to choose from...really liked that. Dining experience was great!!!
Tantan Men was AWESOME!!  I have that every time and be happy happy.  Garlic and plain Gyoza were really good too.
Great food and great atmosphere.
Food was alright.  Assorted for over 30 minutes for a table and was not worth the wait. The upside is their service is great!

I had raman at different places but this is my new favorite. Simple but delicious. Wish I had a couple more pieces of meat in the raman but I am definitely coming back to try out the rest of the delicacies. My wife had the special fried rice which was equally well made.
Place is small and can get busy at certain times. I've eaten here before concerts and the food is always tasty and comes out pretty quickly. Staff is always friendly and efficient.
All the broths are superb (I'm not a fan of tomatoes so I haven't tried that one yet). Pretty much the Go-To Spot for Ramen. I've tried so much places on Honolulu and this one stands out the most.
Got the spicy black truffle ramen, highly recommend

Let me start by saying that I need to go back and try more of the menu. The (Black) Garlic Tonkotsu is phenomenal straight up, and pure heaven with 3x spice. FWIW, you can get 10x spicy for free and pay for more. Lunacy! Friendly service too and the high tables outside are my favorite place to sit here.
Dog friendly ramen place. Reasonable prices with great service.
Great ramen and gyoza!! Will definitely be back. Service was great too!!

Always good and delicious Service is quick and courteous. Food always hoy and delivered as doo. As it is put up to be delivered. This ramen joint is unlike any that I've tasted. Even pkg is plentiful. On the street or behind of the bldg pkg. Be ready for a dam good meal that doesn't bankrupt you
Awesome Ramen! Just like in Japan. Try the black garlic ramen. Usually go to this spot few times a month. Check it out!
Delicious ramen and gyoza, great place to eat before going to Blaisdell.
All the portions here are perfect. This place is definitely a place to eat.

We love junpuu! Generous portions and amazing ramen. I do think that an extra $2.50 for a tiny handful of spinach (seasonal greens) is 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️ but the deliciousness of their food excuses it. I got seasonal veggies the first time and the extra money felt worth it. I recommend the garlic gyoza as a pupu. We’ve had the shoyu, miso, spicy tonkotsu,, and tantan men ramens and have always been satisfied. Validated parking or paid street parking. They have gluten free noodles for an extra $4. Highly recommend!

Their portions run on the smaller side in my experience, but the bowls are sufficiently filling if you order a side to either solo or share. Do not make the mistake I did and order 10/10 spicy level unless you're a total freak because that was too spicy and I consider myself just above casual chili head. The server fairly warned me, but do do some places where the max isn't barely spicy - only way to really know is try. At least now I know they're not messing around but next time I might get a 7 or 8 to enjoy the broth's flavors more. Very friendly service. Good parking in back.
Really delicious ramen here. Also vegan, vegetarian and GF options.
Good noodles, some spicy enough to clear the sinuses. Friendly staff, quick service during lunch. Not a lot of seating, so it fills up at times
My favorite ramen place. Great curry too!
The broth in the ramen is so flavorful it's delicious.! The char siu quesadillas and homemade potato chips were awesome too.
Great ramen every time I go. Just note, it gets spicy very quickly as you move up the scale.

This Japanese ramen restaurant is the best of best in Hawaii ramen place! Really Really tasty!!! This restaurant makes not just salty like other ramen stores in Hawaii. Soup is Amazing!! My favorites are Donkotsu(with Agitama egg) and Tantan ramen. If you enjoy the spicy, you can order Tantan ramen to make more strong spicy! Workers are so kind to their customers. I visit here once a week :) Great!

This place has the best garlic gyoza.  They use garlic flakes that they import.  I order that with the spicy miso ramen then I put the garlic flakes in my ramen. 🤓So ono! And the service is always so good and friendly. They always ready to talk story then leave you alone once your food comes. Lol One thing I will mention is they put MSG in their ramen so if you get migraines you might want to steer clear of this place.

Stopped in for lunch a year ago on vacation. Thought about the Tan Tan salad for a year and made it a point to come back for lunch. Arrived around noon, just ahead of the lunch crowd. The place was the same with friendly staff and lunch came pretty quick. Lunch for two ran just  about $33.00 for salads and water. Clean and nice decor. Close to several tourists spots. Street parking was convenient. Bring some change.

I've been on the ramen binge for awhile and tried this place a few months back then again with my sister this time.   Had the spicy tonkatsu ramen, level ONE spicy.  Def high enough level for me.   Was good.   Shared the gyoza.  Was good also.   Had a coworker that tried level 15!!  Holy moly!  I don't think he finish the ramen 😳
Incredible depth of flavor! Loved every bite!

Best Ramen on Oahu. 13 dollars for so much char siu and even an Ajitama egg with menma and savory veggies. Friendly staff. Its like a 2nd home where i can stop by and eat a filling meal. Miso is the best ive had in my life. Owner is Japanese and it shows in his food. Recommend Tonkotsu, Miso and Tan Tan. There is also Vegetarian Options as well!!!
Really good. Only four stars because I think five star ratings are suspicious.
this might be the best ramen I've ever had.  I've never had a tomatoes based stock.  the potatoes chips were fresh cooked. 1

For homemade Japanese meals in a homey atmosphere, come to Junpuu. There are a lot of ramen options in Hawaii and this is a good one. They offer vegetarian options for their ramen, but it tastes like there’s peanut in it. Tastes good though, just ask about it in case you have allergies. The only other broth option is pork, no chicken broth. Terrific selection of pupu and attentive service as well.
10x spicy is awesome
The broth for the tomato ramen is really light and they even give you cheese to put in it!  The noodles are nice and chewy.
The tomato ramen was pretty good. It has a western spin to it. I got the meat option. It’s basically like marinaré based pasta but flavored nicely. The staff were also really nice.

Best ramen on the island. I like spicy food and they have the spiciest ramen I can find. They use pepper concentrates which make for a real kick. I get the x20 spicy and that will knock most people's socks off. They have up to x100 which I would not recommend unless you enjoy sitting on the toilet for the next three days.

Great Ramen place. Huge parking lot in the back enter through Young street. Seating indoor and out. The service is fast and friendly.  I like their Miso Raman, both noodle and broth are always excellent. I also like the Gyoza and home made fresh potato chips. However, the noodle portion are average. If you are hungry it’s better to get a “Large Ramen” (off menu option), where you’ll get a large bowl with more noodle and broth.  Else if you just order “extra noodle”, you will get noodle in a separate bowl without broth. Overall great place to have Ramen. My new favor Ramen place.
First time there and I've got to say that the broth is really good. I don't normally drink my broth, but I finished today's. Great atmosphere and friendly service.
Amazing ramen and all levels of spice.
Supreme
Small place with big service and terrific tasting fresh to made food!  The noodles and the soup are terrific.
(Translated by Google) Well, it wasn't bad. The taste and price are much better than eating in Waikiki.  (Original) まぁ、悪くなかったです。 ワイキキで食べるより味も値段もかなりマシ。
The soup in the Tokyo tonkotsu ramen is superb.
Excellent food
Food is average.  Don't care much for the soup base.

I keep coming back because not only is the food good and consistent, but I feel comfortable and welcomed. One of the few BYOB places in this neighborhood.  Lots of parking in the back and very easy for anyone that is handicapped. 5PM is the magic time to come and park.
Quaint restaurant with incredible ramen and dashi.  The fon were ness of the ramen was perfect; a slight chew at the start then softens after a few minutes...perfection!

You gotta love the food here... My favorite by far is the vegetable tabtsn ramen.. with extra seasonal veggies. I'm still upping the spiciness.. and I like spicy. So far I haven't maxed my rear end out yet...

I am seriously addicted to this place.  Love everything about it and the service is excellent.

Not many ramen shops offer vegetarian options, but Junpuu offers two. Both seem to use a tasty tomato miso base. We opted for the vegetarian tantan men which included spinach, sweet potato, corn, and bamboo along with a generous portion of noodles. While the taste profile may not be traditional, it os tasty!

Great ramen across from a nice park and Blaisdell.  Outdoor seating welcomes dogs.  Last call is at 9.  Food is usually quick and service is always friendly. They seem to run the place with a pretty small crew so sometimes they get slow. The char-siu is occasionally real fatty. A bit expensive too; before tip, the bill usually sits around $20pp on my visits.  Their spice scale is insane, the level 10 (low end of their ghost pepper range)is among the spiciest dishes I have ever had, and they go to 100.  The restaurant is a small, open space.  I highly recommend.

On a weekday night it's one of my favorite ramen stops. The Tokyo tonkotsu reminds me of my old ramen flavor in Japan.  Noodles r chewy and cooked just right and the soup is neither too watery or too thick. Try it and u will agree.

A great place for a quick bite.  The restaurant is a little small but it's not hard to get a seat right away.  Service is a little slow, but the food makes up for it.  There are also some seats right outside of the restaurant, which is nice when it's not too hot outside.  I would recommend eating here.

Solid spot to grab a bowl of decent ramen. I got the garlic miso ramen and added the ajitama egg. BF got the tantan men and upgraded to "special" (egg and extra char-siu). We both loved the flavor of our broth and the chewy texture of our noodles. We also split a gyoza - those were just average - but next time I'll try the garlic gyoza instead.  Great setting: a few community tables, a couple 2-seaters, a couple of 2-seaters on the lanai, a glass wall with an open entrance, and interesting light fixtures that reminded me of a beach shower with light bulbs attached to where the water would come out.  We arrived on a Saturday at about 3pm, which was a nice time since there was only a handful of other people. On weekends, there is parking at the Medical Arts Building (off Young Street - upon entry, look for sign indicating which # stalls are for Junpuu). They have awesome hours too - open daily and close at 10pm (last call at 9)!

My daughter and I went today and we had the shoyu ramen and the gyoza. The ramen was so delicious and the broth was very tasty. The gyoza was the best I have ever tasted. Out of this world. Definetly this will be our go to ramen place from now on. The iced tea was good too.  We were so happy to find this place.
